<br>
Earring of Twisted Leaves AC:2 Wis  1 HP/MANA  35 Effect: Scale of Wolf<br>
Earring of Woven Bark AC:2 HP/MANA  35 Effect: Snare<br>
A Hollowed Pixie's Rib AC:1 Wis  4 HP/MANA  20<br>
<br>
I am curious to know what you all think of this problem, and maybe you can help me come up with a solution. Thanks in advance Grovers! <p><center><img border="0" src="http://63.226.234.45/megaman.gif" width="250" height="100"><br>
<font size="-2"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=29147" target="_blank">MegaBuzz</a>
| 56 Preserver | <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/bdarkbloodmessageboard" target="_blank">&lt;Darkblood&gt;</a></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujentrikenaspenbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jentriken Aspenbark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/12/02 1:04:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26382.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My little problem</span><hr size=1> at 60 1 wis is 6 mana over 200. i assume if you can fight in chardok your at 200 wis or slightly over.<br>
<br>
so your pixie rib is 20 hp, 44 mana (give or take), and 1 ac.<br>
<br>
so the tradeoff between pixie rib and snare earring is as such.<br>
<br>
for 9 mana you lose 15 hp and 1 ac. also a nice no mana effect.<br>
<br>
i'd take the earring of woven bark, but that's just me.<br>
if your not 60 yet you lose even less mana changing over.<br>
 <p>Baron Jentriken Aspenbark
<BR><BR>
Heirophant
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustormhaven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormhaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/12/02 6:33:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26382.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web2.airmail.net/naomi/amalgam/forum/stormhaven.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My little problem</span><hr size=1> I see you're not at 255 WIS yet according to your Magelo profile.  Well, seeing that the Rib gives you both a WIS and a Mana bonus, I would suggest the  Leaves/Rib combo.  A 1 AC bonus is going to do you between Jack and Squat.  The Rib has 15 less mana, but adds 4 WIS - which gets you up to 242 if your profile is accurate.  <br>
<br>
You've got your epic, so I'm assuming you're not using the snare effect on the Woven Bark earring.  If you were using the snare from the earring constantly, it might be worth keeping it on - but seeing that it's snare instead of &quot;en&quot;snare, once again the overall usefulness is cut down a bit.  However, having a free snare isn't bad as long as it's fast casting - nice trinket to have when you're OOM in a exp group.  If it's slow casting, once again, you mine as well use your epic.<br>
<br>
So, if you only have those earrings to choose from, I'd say go with the Leaves/Rib selection.  The best idea would be to start working toward your PotC earrings though. <p><body link="#FFFFFF" vlink="#CCCCCC">

